<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.170411>
    dc:description "FIGURES 6 – 8. Trichromothrips formosus n. sp. (female): (6) Head & pronotum (median pale areas on head and pronotum indicated by dotted lines); (7) Antennal segments I – VIII (right); (8) Mesonotum & metascutum. Scale bar = 0.04 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/170411/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.170412>
    dc:description "FIGURES 11 – 14. Trichromothrips formosus n. sp. (male). Abdominal segments: (11) Terga IX – X; (12) Tergum IX (left­dorsal aspect); (13) Sternum VI; (14) Genitalia (left aspect). hy = hypomere; pa = paramere. Scale bar 0.04 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/170412/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

